activityList.description: Tired. Saw a mink near the trail.
Forgot to start my watch
Watch died.

I was about halfway through the run and I was thinking of the other day when I had something attack me from the trees. I got to the spot and I thought to myself this must be about where it was and WHAM something grabbed a hold of the top of my head, messed my hair. Ive bent forward and waved my hands frantically above my head, but theres nothing. I looked up and around me, but I saw nothing. I backed away a few steps and then I saw an owl. He flew to a branch and turned and looked at me. It edged close to the side of the tree so that it was hidden by its silhouette. I turned and started jogging and came upon a man who was coming the other way. I told him an owl attacked me and warned him to be careful. He probably thought I was crazy.

I think I was attacked by an owl this morning on my run. I was running on a trail that borders the backyard of some houses. All of a sudden I was struck on the back right part of my head and neck. It made me yell. My first thought was, I had been struck by something thrown, but I had heard nothing. Nothing in the air. Nothing hit the ground. I waved my hand above my head, and there was nothing there. It hit hard, a quick strike, but without much weight. I have a few small lacerations on the back right side of my neck and head. I guess it mustve seen my ponytail bouncing around and thought it was supper.

Felt rough today. Started to pour down rain halfway through. Ran across a frightened woman in her car. The car wouldnt start, windows down. Someone was going to get help. I wished her luck and kept going.
Official result 5:25.883
I woke up feeling pretty terrible this morning tired, back hurt, throat hurt. I shook it off in the next hour so I went for a run.
My back is not great.
3 hills at the end.
This was a good one. It feels like Im starting to get somewhere. Ive been running slower, more often, and feeling better.
Heart rate was at 140 after half mile. Over 160 with half mile to go. I need a slower start. Monitoring heart rate during the run is helpful.
Pre-meet Masters 800 with Craig.

57 degrees. Cloudy but nice to be out. I cant remember the last time it was this nice. A red tail hawk flew over the trail. It was carrying some small animal. It landed on a branch to my right and turned to look down at me as I passed.
Wind 24 mph. That was not the route to run.
Not feeling very good but its too nice outside.
